messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 7/13/2004 3:47:14 PM Eastern Daylight Time,
webinfusion@... writes:

The website has the dates of Aug 27-29 but no schedule of events posted.
What time on Friday does the conference begin? What time does it end on Sunday?
Is it a very casual (clothing) event?<<<

Last year we started at noon on Friday. Registration packet pick-up was from
9-12. I will probably end about 2:00 or so on Sunday, but we have a Whale
Watch scheduled that afternoon---I don't know what time. It's on the site. A lot
of folks hang around another day or two just to connect some more. No one
wants to leave! <G>

It's VERY casual!

Be patient with Kathryn about not posting the schedual yet. I've warned her
not to! <BWG> Things can change so much between now and August 27---she needs
to keep it as flexible as possible. The schedual will be posted a week or
two before----at the earliest! But plan to be there Friday morning and to leave
no earlier than Sunday afternoon.

~Kelly, former conference diva
